\ls6\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What\'92s your personal background and how did you came to be director of The Library ?\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 I had a four years experience as Analyst in the Israeli Intelligence Corps (army). Then I graduated in PPE \'97 Philosophy, Politics and Economics in Tel Aviv University. It trains people to take part in Public Sector, by giving them economic tools to reshape policies. I was particularly interested in urban planning and developing better policies for better cities. My first experiences in this field make me feel that it was missing of tech in public sector. So I joined\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.insights.us/"}}{\fldrslt \ul insights.us}}, both a startup and a consulting company from Jerusalem to disrupt public participation.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 They developed a platform to facilitate open discussions in civil society. Using widely open questions, not closed questions like survey studies, to get natural feedback from the citizens, and algorithms to analyse the feedback with natural language processing.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 We had contracts in USA, Canada, UK, Israel, we had offices in Berlin to work with Germany and Austria. It was a good run, leading big consultation on big cities, but public sector move very slowly and pays very few. At a moment, the company have had to make a financial choice and stop the platform development to focus on consultancy contracts. I left the company, same as other colleagues. I have been contacted by Tel Aviv municipality which I worked with at insights, and they proposed me to be the director of The Library.\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Which goals are you trying to achieve with The Library ?\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 The Library is an urban innovation center managed by the Community Department of the Municipality of Tel Aviv. We are considered as a youth center, but we host startups at early stage which try to improve life in the city. We do not call ourselves Smart-City because we do not want to be associated with infrastructure innovation only.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 What we are achieving in The library is more about facilitating communities and bringing neighborhoods together, supporting education to technology. We look for an impact on anything that could make the city better. We are inspired by the model of a City As A Service and try to implement it in Tel Aviv Municipality.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 We provide our incubated startups diverse services such as mentorship, workshops, and meetings with experts and/or inhabitants. And we also orient the startups to help them find what can be really interesting for the city and the inhabitants.\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What\'92s your strategy to make the city a better place to live-in ?\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 1. We create facilities to connect the people.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 2. We provide access to data owned by the city, we help the startups to prioritize their needs to give them the right data at the right moment and we assist them in the use of raw data.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 3. We help them to create a pilot project, to test their products in real-city situations.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Commonly, we try to make the city of Tel Aviv less expensive, by supporting a less consumer-based society\'85\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 How\'92s your relationship with the other stakeholders and who are your major supporters ?\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 As a public service, we are paid and supported by the municipality.\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Do you target any specific transformation of the city that would be concretely experienced by the inhabitants ?\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 As for my experience, I wanted to transform the public sector, to make it better for people and more \'93Techy\'94. This is exactly what I am doing with The Library.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 I work in collaboration with CityZone, Department of Communication, and The Platform, Tel Aviv Global. We are the three main actors of the IT innovation on the city, each of us depending on a different city department. All of our operating system is a sort of big consultancy of the citizens. They are a network of innovation places working all together for the city.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 By challenging us and exchanging together, we are concretely achieving the transverse innovation out of the municipal department silos.\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 As you experienced it from the startup side and now from the municipality side, what do you thing about public participation 2.0 ?Public participation and widely democratic processes will have to evolve in collaborative decision-making. Using web tools seems to be the most relevant way to do it, but no good solution has been found yet to do it at a large scale. Even if we know the need to bring the technology into democracy, the civic-tech do not bring valuable insights so far. Blockchain, AI, Machine learning are very promising but for the moment the best way to achieve citizen consultation is by analog processes such roundtables, surveys, workshops with inhabitants\'85 It is time consuming and can\'92t be scaled up because it needs a personal presence of an expert or a public servant or an animator of debate, but nothing really work so good for the moment and we have to continue to practice a little bit of everything to find the best way to do it.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://zencity.io/"}}{\fldrslt \ul ZenCity}}\'a0and Insights are the biggest actors working in that field in Israel. Obviously, tech is a part of their solution but not the main part.\cb1 \
