\ls8\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What\'92s your personal background ? How did you came to work at SaronaHub ?\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 I\'92m 20 years old, after High School, instead of military service, I chose to do a sort of civil service 1 year or 2 years. I heard about this specific place by a friend who has been accepted in the center, so I tried as well. I\'92m more centered on technology, she is more centered on coordination.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Civil service is not paid, but regarded as volunteering. We receive a place in a shared public flat with other peoples who do the same. We are 7 young people of the same age. Everything is paid (water, electricity, internet, etc. ) and we receive 800 shekel a month which is not enough to live but we still get support from the parents to start.\cb1 \
\ls8\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What is SaronaHub and what king of mission are you achieving here ?SaronaHub is about empowering young people. The whole name is Sarona Municipal Teens and Youth Center for Entrepreneurship and Technology. The age of the public is grade so middle-school and high -school so from 11 to 18 years old. They come by themselves mainly and sometimes are oriented by the school. They have heard about us by internet, social media and word to mouth.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 We also have some cooperation programs with the schools. In particular we promote an Entrepreneurial Excellence Program in partnership with the Education Department of Tel Aviv which recommend our center.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 SaronaHub depends on the Department of Youth and Teens which is under the Community Department.\cb1 \
\ls8\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What\'92s the usual route for a young who come here ?\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 So we basically offer the open space to work, it\'92s completely free, and open on weekdays from 3 to 8 pm. They just come, without registering or asking anyone. They can come alone, with friends, to work on a project or just study their homework. We do not offer support on studies by the way.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 We propose content and advice on entrepreneurship and technologies. We organize events and meetings on these topics, depending on the demand from the users in the space. We provide workshops animation, content diffusion, and professional courses on different topics : coding, entrepreneurship, design, digital marketing, industrial design, financial education, cyber-security.\cb1 \
\ls8\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What\'92s your strategy to reach them and animate the young networks ?The most effective right now has been social medias : Instagram in particular (we receive and answer direct messages), secondarily Facebook and our own website, and the word to mouth works as well.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 We also go to schools at the beginning of the year to present ourselves, the hub and invite the kids to come. By time to time we also organize kind of parties on our thematic. Some days ago we had 150 standing persons.\cb1 \
\ls8\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Do you have professional projects that come out of here ?\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 In a wide range, yes. More are social projects and initiatives that people want to implement. For example, a high impact project from last year has been to create football teams for girls in elementary schools. It opened in 2 different schools last year and has led to a tournament. This year, 30 feminine football groups opened in the schools of the city. It\'92s a big success.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 We are also hosting a Composting Restaurant Program : the team is working with local restaurants and the municipality to use the compost for the gardens of Tel Aviv. They already have physical space from the municipality and some restaurants but it is not so, easy to move the trash from one place to another.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 A teen came here to study marketing and design and now he have a small service company with contractors. He did connections and branched out in this space.\cb1 \
\ls8\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Do you make a connection between the kids and the tech industry ?\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Yes, most of the contents of the meetups and workshops are for adults, so when some young from the Hub are very successful in their project, we bring them to tours in Google, Microsoft, Facebook, these companies are present in Tel Aviv, so we show this world to the kids.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 They also benefit for a mentorship if they need a specific help in a particular field.\cb1 \
\ls8\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Are you using a web platform to manage and empower your network?Actually we do not, it is kind of messy with a lot of google sheets, but I am working on a graphic database platform website : Airtable, a no-code solution.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 We plan to implement it with tablets at the entrance, for the kids to enter their personal information, both connected to their profile and to the data center to assist them better.\cb1 \
\ls8\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What are the main reason for a young to stop coming here?\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 The number 1 reason is the army, usually we they start the army they do not have time or interest to pursue what they were doing here. And before the army they start to prepare the high-school diploma, so they are also very busy at this time.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Another common reason is a lost of interest, not specifically for us, but teens explore a lot of areas, and sometimes, they want to create a startup one year, and next year they prefer to create a music band rather.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 So we try to lead the projects by community, like this if someone stops, the project can continue with the ones who still want to engage.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Theoretically, their success could be a reason to scale up and take their own offices too.\cb1 \
\ls8\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 How many teens did you accompanied ?\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 We had about 200 members who come here regularly, at least 2 times a month. Some can come twice a week but they are not always regulars, it come by phase. We are OK with this, we do not oblige anyone.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 40 to 50 projects has been accompanied widely.\cb1 \
\ls8\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What would be the next steps for the future of SaronaHub?\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 The city will open a similar hub in the southern part of the city to reach out the poorest class kids and empower the communities of these districts. The whole concept is evolving on more creative and makers spaces. More about game and social and giving them tools and education training.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 It is gonna be another team in the Hub but we work with them to share experience and help manage it. We offer help to say how to start. No compete with them but try to be complementary.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 SaronaHub itself think about growing because sometimes it can be very crowded : the working capacity is 56 and for event we can host 150 standing people. But we do not want to come to this day where we will have to say some kids they can\'92t enter because we\'92re full.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 We would like more projects to come out of the space. Even if we do not take any fees or money, neither ask the kids to promote SaronaHub, for personal satisfaction, we would like to attract more people and help them in success. And we would like to attract kids widely, we do not want to be reserved for the kids talented in tech, genius at coding or with parents working at Google etc. We want all the kids to feel welcome to join and learn about tech and startups.\cb1 \
